Sentencas: Novel composite materials based on mixtures of samarium-doped ceria (SDC)-carbonate were examined for use as electrolyte materials in low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LTSOFCs) operating at 400-600 degrees C.
Titulo: SDC-carbonate composite electrolytes for low-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The composite electrolytes showed high ion conductivity at evaluated temperatures.
Titulo: SDC-carbonate composite electrolytes for low-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: Composition and calcination temperature were found to affect the morphology and conductivity of the composite electrolytes greatly.
Titulo: SDC-carbonate composite electrolytes for low-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: During fuel cell operation, water was observed at both electrodes, indicating that the new electrolyte materials conduct both oxygen ions and proton simultaneously.
Titulo: SDC-carbonate composite electrolytes for low-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: According to fuel cell performance, these composite electrolytes are chemically stable, which is an attractive prospect in LTSOFC applications.
Titulo: SDC-carbonate composite electrolytes for low-temperature SOFCs
